Akthough it's true this recipe has no Thai flavors, it's still delicious. I've made these for guests several times, they love them. Don't try to grill them however, they are best broiled, which makes them extra crispy.

Rating: 4
I have to say I was pleasantly surprised by the outcome of these wings. I wouldn't change a thing on the recipe. Marinating overnight with the oil/garlic is key to this. The sauce mixture is just the right balance to offset the salt and pepper you had on while broiling. I made this for myself just to try it out because I wasn't sure what to expect, as it sounded too simple to have good flavor. I will try this out on guests next, and sure it will be a hit.

